column15: Unyq Design, Inc. designs, manufactures, and sells 3D printed prosthetic covers and accessories for amputees. It offers customized prosthetic covers for men, women, and kids. The company also operates a direct-to-consumer ecommerce site that allows amputees to design 3D printed custom protective covers and other ornamentations for their prosthetic legs. It sells its products online. The company was founded in 2014 and is based in San Francisco, California with studios in San Francisco, California; and Seville, Spain.

column15: WePow, Inc. develops and delivers Web and mobile video interviewing platforms. It offers various solutions to engage, screen, and hire candidates for various industries in the United States and internationally. WePow, Inc. was formerly known as Wowzer, Inc. and changed its name to WePow, Inc. in September 2013. The company was founded in 2010 and is based in Sunnyvale, California.

Toutatis Aztec Solutions provides business solutions for middle-market companies in the United States and internationally. It offers financial/accounting/ERP software, customer relationship management, document imaging, and vertical and industry solutions. The company provides software installations and customizations, business process consulting, software training (onsite or remote), software enhancements and upgrades, software development, data backup and storage, disaster recovery, cloud computingapplication hosting, virtualization, desktop and server support, networking and IT support, annual system reviews, systems integration, and hardware platform services. It also offers remote and onsite managed services. The company serves customers in various industries, such as healthcare, hospitality and retail, inventory management, oil and gas, energy, professional/financial services, supply chain, and wholesale distribution. Toutatis Aztec Solutions was formerly known as Aztec Systems, Inc. and changed its name on April 3, 2013. The company was founded in 1991 and is based in Carrollton, Texas with additional offices in Austin and San Antonio, Texas; and Oklahoma City and Tulsa, Oklahoma. Toutatis Aztec Solutions operates as a subsidiary of glendonTodd Capital LLC.

Tagga Media, Inc. provides cross-channel campaign management software and marketing services. It operates Tagga, a cloud-based platform that leverages Web, mobile, and social media to connect users with every member of their audience across the marketing mix. The company's platform enables clients to build, launch, monitor, and report campaign performance across various media. Its platform enables users to engage with their consumers by capturing their attention through mobile and social integration; building a custom campaign; and promoting the brand cross-channel. In addition, the company offers various services, such as strategy development, tactical plan development, and media buying and planning; application and landing page development for Facebook, mobile, and desktop; SMS, QR code, and email marketing campaigns; and design and development for mobile sites, media advertisements, and applications. Tagga Media, Inc. was founded in 2008 and is based in Vancouver, Canada.

StackEngine, Inc. builds Docker management and automation software. The company operates a platform that allows organizations to deploy, manage, and scale resilient Docker applications. Its Docker software enables product teams to bootstrap Docker into production; discover, visualize, and manage small to large scale Docker deployments; and automate change and configuration management for containers. The company was incorporated in 2014 and is based in Austin, Texas.

AtHoc is the pioneer and leading provider of enterprise-class, network-based mass notification systems for the security, life safety and defense sectors. As the #1 supplier to the U.S. Federal Government, AtHoc protects over 2 million personnel across U.S. Military, Homeland Security and other government agencies. Additional sectors served include healthcare, higher education, and large commercial organizations. AtHocâ€™s products are deployed within a cloud-based architecture and used for physical security, force protection, personnel accountability, recall and regulatory compliance. AtHoc has partnered with market leaders including Microsoft, Cisco, Harris, Northrop Grumman, MIR3, Lockheed Martin and others to bring these notification solutions to the public and commercial markets.
